subSubSection.paragraph:
Epigyne with copulatory openings in large J-shaped epigynal ridges (
Fig. 59
); copulatory ducts relatively thick, initially curving mesally, then directed posteriorly along midline, looping dorsally and laterally before entering lateral teardrop-shaped primary spermathecae along their interior margin; bursae oval, similar in size to primary spermathecae (
Fig. 60
).

Palpal femur with stout thumb tip-like ventral apophysis; patella with small subtriangular retrolateral ridge; tibia with tibial apophysis short and triangular in ventral view, broad and ridge-like in retrolateral view; embolus larger than in congeners, S-shaped, width larger than ½ width of tegulum at midpoint, tip curved and directed retrolaterally (
Figs 61–63
).
